<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1155,141,271]" box="[160,276,141,167]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,141,167]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1155,141,271]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Shell small, elongate; sutures canaliculate. Teleoconch whorls with axial ribs, rounded or erect as flanges. Aperture elongate. Outer lip not thickened; short, well-defined, very shallow anterior canal present; posterior canal absent. No varices or ventrolateral varix.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,318,899]" box="[160,262,318,344]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,318,344]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,318,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">
In Peru, 
<taxonomicName authority="DeVries, 2019" authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" box="[254,373,355,379]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[254,373,355,379]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[381,487,355,379]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known from just one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="DeVries, 2019" authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" box="[860,1115,355,379]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="segmentata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[860,1115,355,379]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea segmentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
In most characters, the Caballas Formation species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Perrilliat et al." authorityName="Perrilliat" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Pachychilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lawtoni" subGenus="Pachychiloides">
<emphasis box="[1029,1155,389,413]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychilus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[167,326,424,448]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychiloides</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[345,426,424,448]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">lawtoni</emphasis>
Perrilliat et al.
</taxonomicName>
<date box="[601,670,424,448]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" value="2008-01">, 2008</date>
; a common species in Eocene fluvial red and green mudstones of the Carroza Formation of 
<collectingCountry box="[764,844,459,483]" name="Mexico" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Perrilliat MCi Vega FJi Espinosa Bi Naranjo-Garcia E" box="[861,1090,459,483]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" pagination="255 - 266" refId="ref25877" refString="Perrilliat MCi Vega FJi Espinosa Bi Naranjo-Garcia E. 2008. Late Cretaceous and Paleogene freshwater gastropods from northeastern Mexico. J Paleontol. 82 (2): 255 - 266." type="journal article" year="2008">Perrilliat et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The Carroza Formation specimens, for which no complete apertures are preserved, may not be properly placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[428,584,528,552]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Pachychilidae</taxonomicName>
. All modern pachychilids, excepting 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeusi 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeusi" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Faunus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[1021,1155,528,552]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Faunus ater</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
, have apertures without anterior or posterior canals (
<bibRefCitation author="Glaubrecht Mi von Rintelen T" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" pagination="415 - 435" refId="ref23862" refString="Glaubrecht Mi von Rintelen T. 2003. Systematicsi molecular genetics and historical zoogeography of the viviparous freshwater gastropod Pseudopotamis (Cerithioideai Pachychilidae): a relic on the Torres Strait Islandsi Australia. Zool Scr. 32 (5): 415 - 435." type="journal article" year="2003">Glaubrecht and von Rintelen 2003</bibRefCitation>
). This absence of apertural canals is true for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Whitei 1876)" baseAuthorityName="Whitei" baseAuthorityYear="1876" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Pachychilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cleburni" subGenus="Pachychiloides">
<emphasis box="[862,876,597,621]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[896,1055,597,621]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychiloides</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1069,1155,597,621]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">cleburni</emphasis>
(White, 1876)
</taxonomicName>
from the Cretaceous Bear River Formation of Wyoming, a species with which 
<bibRefCitation author="Perrilliat MCi Vega FJi Espinosa Bi Naranjo-Garcia E" box="[235,467,667,691]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" pagination="255 - 266" refId="ref25877" refString="Perrilliat MCi Vega FJi Espinosa Bi Naranjo-Garcia E. 2008. Late Cretaceous and Paleogene freshwater gastropods from northeastern Mexico. J Paleontol. 82 (2): 255 - 266." type="journal article" year="2008">Perrilliat et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName box="[596,885,667,691]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Pachychilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lawtoni" subGenus="Pachychiloides">
<emphasis box="[596,609,667,691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[630,788,667,691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychiloides</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[804,885,667,691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">lawtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Eocene 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="segmentata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea segmentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, which so closely resembles the Carroza Formation species, has a short and very shallow anterior canal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,318,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">
It is proposed herein that 
<taxonomicName box="[523,746,771,795]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Pachychilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lawtoni">
<emphasis box="[523,746,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychilus lawtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Carroza Formation and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" box="[160,429,805,829]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="segmentata">
<emphasis box="[160,429,805,829]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea segmentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Caballas Formation are congeneric and that 
<taxonomicName box="[160,381,840,864]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pachychilidae" genus="Pachychilus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lawtoni">
<emphasis box="[160,381,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Pachychilus lawtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
be transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="DeVries, 2019" authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" box="[609,728,840,864]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1576" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[609,728,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species of 
<taxonomicName authority="DeVries, 2019" authorityName="DeVries" authorityYear="2019" box="[988,1107,840,864]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" genus="Caballasea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="1576" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[988,1107,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567">Caballasea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[299,441,875,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Potamididae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="1567" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Potamididae</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of an anterior canal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
